docs.abstract: The Trump administration said China had agreed to make the potent drug a controlled substance, a move that would have major implications for America’s opioid crisis.
docs.snippet: The Trump administration said China had agreed to make the potent drug a controlled substance, a move that would have major implications for America’s opioid crisis.
docs.lead_paragraph: BEIJING — China vows to stem the supply of the powerful opioid fentanyl flowing into the United States. It pledges to target exports of fentanyl-related substances bound for the United States that are prohibited there, while sharing information with American law-enforcement authorities.

headline.main: Trump Says China Will Curtail Fentanyl. The U.S. Has Heard That Before.
headline.print_headline: China Gives Lip Service  On Fentanyl

docs.abstract: Less than halfway through April, companies have announced plans to close 5,994 stores, above the 5,854 that shut last year.

docs.abstract: The end of the so-called quantitative easing effort is a milestone for the euro and a signal that the European Central Bank is confident enough in the eurozone’s health.
docs.snippet: The end of the so-called quantitative easing effort is a milestone for the euro and a signal that the European Central Bank is confident enough in the eurozone’s health.
docs.lead_paragraph: Frankfurt — One of the biggest money-printing programs of all time, a geyser of cash that may have prevented the collapse of the eurozone, will officially end in a few weeks in a slow-motion wrap-up that reflects lingering risks to the region.

headline.main: Europe’s Central Bank Ends One of the Biggest Money-Printing Programs Ever
headline.print_headline: Euro Bank Closes Book On Stimulus

docs.abstract: From meritorious public service for coverage of the deadly shooting rampage at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School to a special citation to the “Queen of Soul,” here is the full list of winners and finalists.
docs.snippet: From meritorious public service for coverage of the deadly shooting rampage at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School to a special citation to the “Queen of Soul,” here is the full list of winners and finalists.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Sun Sentinel’s sweeping coverage of the causes and consequences of the deadly mass shooting at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School in Parkland, Fla., shaped the national gun safety debate and prompted changes in local policies. The paper addressed a culture of leniency at Broward County schools, blunders by the sheriff’s office in responding to the attack and attempts by officials to mask their failures.

docs.abstract: She held a front-office title and had an active philanthropic career. Her four children with George Steinbrenner are now general partners of the team.

docs.lead_paragraph: Joan Steinbrenner, a philanthropist and vice-chairwoman of the Yankees and the widow of George Steinbrenner, who had a tumultuous but hugely successful run as the team’s principal owner and chairman, died on Tuesday at her home in Tampa, Fla. She was 83.

headline.main: Joan Steinbrenner, 83, Yankees Vice-Chairwoman and Owner’s Widow, Dies
headline.print_headline: Joan Steinbrenner, 83, Official Of Yankees and Philanthropist
